The Canyons:

- On a day when it's raining in the valley, take the bus to the desert and enter Sandy's Oasis after 6pm. Agree to help, and the sidewalk warp will appear leading to the Canyonlands. 
- The very first time you enter, gather as many rainpuffs as you can following the warps. Bring at least one rainpuff back to Sandy, who will give you a recipe.
- Make the tea in the recipe, and bring it back to Sandy's Oasis (anytime) to trigger another cutscene.
- After this, the sidewalk will lead to the Canyonlands all the time, and they will have "shifted" from the last time you were there. There will also be a southern exit from the Canyonlands that leads down to the Trolley Pond 
(if you tried to go up before, the bush that was in the way will be gone). 
- If you're ever lost on what "stage" the Canyons are at, the man with his donkey will give you a hint.
- Explore the new Canyonlands map until you reach the "summit" where you'll be blocked by a guy asking riddles. Answer his riddle and the warp will take you home.
- The next day, the Canyons will have shifted again. Explore again, and find another riddle-guy.
- The next day, the Canyons will have changed again. Explore again, and find a secret swimming area that will take to the main area of the desert summit.
- Find the flamingo who runs the shop, and answer a couple final riddles. This will unlock both the shop, and the final Canyonlands map.
- Once you take the warp home, the Canyons will be set at that final map, and a special new forageable will appear all over the Canyon floor. These forageables are coded to be "universally loved" gifts for everyone.
- Bring that forageable to Sandy's Oasis to unlock another tea recipe.
- After this, the purple platform at the Canyon's entrance can be used to go directly back to the Flamingo Shop, which is where you can exchange rainpuffs for recipes, and most importantly: 
- a tortoise egg that can be hatched into a large desert tortoise in a ostrich incubator, for the Barn.
- The tortoises drop eggs, which can be hatched again, or pickled in a preserves jar. They also drop tortoisehell bits, that can be crafted with bone fragments to create tortoiseshell hairpins. These hairpins are especially beloved by a fiew NPCs, including Haley, Emily, Penny, and Krobus.


Ranger Taro/the Meadow:

- The entrance is right above the bridge/cliff to the Flower Dance area; trigger the first cutscene by entering the tent.
- The Ranger's 2-heart scene triggers upon entering the forest on any day OTHER than Fri/Sun (the days the Traveling Merchant is there)
- The 4-heart scene is triggered in the Meadow, on any sunny day between 6am and 6pm.
- For the 6-heart event, you will receive a strange letter in the mail, saying to meet at the Trolly Pond AFTER 6pm.
- If you haven't found the Trolley Pond yet, it's the central crossroads between all the maps, and is directly left of Taro's Meadow following the train tracks.
- For the 8-heart event, enter the Meadow anytime.
- The 10-heart event can only be triggered on a Saturday, in the forest. 
- After this, the Traveling Merchant will appear every Saturday in the Meadow along with her usual Fri/Sun spot.
- There is a final bonus event where the farmer and a group of friends go hiking with Ranger Taro. You must have seen Emily's heart event with the parrot hitting her window, and have brought Leo back to the valley from Ginger Island. 

FIASA/the Cove:

- Start the first cutscene by walking into the boat for the first time, in Stormboat Cove. Koda will explain how the exchange program works, but basically whenever she is at the desk (Tue/Wed/Thu) you can exchange coral for random goods, similiar to the Traveling Merchant.
- On Mondays, Koda does fieldwork; if you haven't repaired the bridge to the tide bools at the beach, she will actually be on the back deck of the boat (and inaccessible unless you have enough hearts). Once you repair the bridge, she'll spend every Monday getting climate readings at the tide pools.
- On Fridays, Koda has a day off from work, and can be found wandering around Pelican Town.
- The boat is gone on the weekends.
- On festival days, the boardwalk leading to the Cove will be gone at the Beach, but you can still access the Cove through the Trolley Pond/Taro's Meadow.
- Trigger the 2-heart event by entering the FIASA boat anytine between 8am and 6pm.
- Trigger Koda's 4-heart event by entering the FIASA boat anytime between 6am and 6pm on Tue/Wed/Thu (her work days).
- After this, the back deck of the boat will be unlocked. It's my favorite place.
- The 6-heart event will trigger on it's own, with Koda approaching you at the farm. This cutscene is MONUMENTALLY important in the back-end code, so if you end up triggering the rest of the 6-heart event without having seen Koda at the farm, I highly reccomend you quit the day. 
- To finish the 6-heart event, go to the FIASA boat anytime before midnight on a weekday.
- This cutscene will end with the introduction of a new character, Captain Inke.
- Captain Inke's first gift to the player is a clutch of turtle eggs, that can be hatched in a coop incubator for island turtles on the farm.
- The turtles drop more eggs, which can be hatched again, or pickled in a preserves jar.
- After this, both Koda and Inke will live in the FIASA boat, with different schedules. Inke will start manning the exchange desk, and Koda will have a little more time to wander around and talk.
- Koda next progression requires the Community Center to be completed. If it isn't completed, there is a 7-heart cutscene at the Bus Stop where she lets you know that her "next stesps" involve the Community Center.
- If it is complete, that 7-heart cutscene will be an invite from Koda to come see her there "when it's all ready."
- The 8-heart event therefore can only be triggered if you have seen the celebration around opening the Community Center. 
- The first scene happens at the Bus Stop on a weekday, with a random traveler who is going to the Community Center. Follow his lead and enter the CC anytime on a weekday.
- This completes Koda's character arc, if you are going platonic. 
- If you want to romance/date her, her 10-heart event is triggered at the Beach, anytime on a weekday.
- If you marry her, Koda will have a Work From Home office and schedule, talking about her work with the Captain, and on Fridays she will still take her "off day" to wander town and go to the Saloon. 
- She will also head to the Beach for special ecological events like the summer green tide.
- If you marry her, Koda has a full 14-heart event that triggers automatically one farm morning ONLY if you have unlocked the farmhouse on Ginger Island. 
- She will let you know that the Captain is taking her on some extended fieldwork that will happen to pass by Ginger Island, and that she'll try to stop by to see you.
- This starts a 50/50 chance to trigger the next cutscene anytime you sleep over at Ginger Island. On a random morning when you exit the Ginger Island farmhouse, Koda's 14-heart adventure will start. It's really special to me haha (A/N)

MEANWHILE, don't forget about Captain Inke!

- The Captain's 2-heart event is tiggered by entering the FIASA boat anytime between 6am and 6pm.
- The Captain does not have a 4-heart event; instead, his 6-heart event is started at anytime entering the FIASA boat. This will take you on an extended mini-adventure.
- The Captain's 10-heart event is the final scene for the entire expansion, and has some pre-reqs: You must have Koda at 8 hearts, Ranger Taro at 10 hearts, Captain Inke at 10 hearts, and have reached the Flamingo Shop in the Canyons.
- The 10-heart event itself will start with Ranger Taro at the farmhouse, on a Saturday or Sunday. Follow through on the conversation by going to Stormboat Cove anytime on a Sat/Sun.
- This will start a long-ish, celebratory cutscene with all of the characters and animals from the entire expansion :)


